<title>USA: Micrografx buys AdvanEdge, will take charge.</title>
<headline>Micrografx buys AdvanEdge, will take charge.</headline>
<dateline>RICHARDSON, Texas 1997-06-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Micrografx Inc said Monday it bought the privately-held AdvanEdge Technologies for about $3.5 million.</p>
<p>Micrografx said it will account for the deal as a purchase, which will result in a charge in the fourth quarter of fiscal year 1997 which ends August 6.</p>
<p>Other costs related to the acquisition will be accounted for in the current fiscal quarter. Micrografx said excluding the one-time charges in the fourth quarter, the acquisition should not be dilutive to future earnings.</p>
<p>As part of the acquisition, Micrografx will expand the existing AdvanEdge staff in a new Portland-based business unit, it said.</p>
